TASK 1:– Setting up the system and ordering the main items.
Write a program to:
use arrays to store the item code, description and price
allow a customer to choose one case, one RAM and one Main Hard Disk Drive
calculate the price of the computer using the cost of the chosen items and the
basic set of components
store and output the chosen items and the price of the computer.

CODE:

Item_code = ['A1', 'A2', 'B1', 'B2', 'B3', 'C1', 'C2', 'C3', 'D1', 'D2', 'E1', 'E2', 'E3', 'F1', 'F2', 'G1', 'G2']
Description = ['Compact', 'Tower', '8GB', '16GB', '32GB', '1 TB HDD', '2TB HDD', '4TB HDD', '240 GB SSD', '240 GB SSD',
               '1 TB HDD', '2TB HDD', '4TB HD', 'DVD/Blu-Ray Player', 'DVD/Blu-Ray Re-written', 'Standard Version',
               'Professional version']
Price = [75, 150, 79.99, 149.99, 299.99, 49.99, 89.99, 129.99, 59.99, 119.99, 49.99, 89.99, 129.99, 50, 100, 100, 175]

Choice1 = input("Please choose one case: ")
Choice2 = input("Please choose one RAM: ")
Choice3 = input("Please choose one HDD: ")

price = 0  # Initialize the price to 0

# Check choices and calculate the price
if Choice1 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice1)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for case.")

if Choice2 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice2)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for RAM.")

if Choice3 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice3)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for HDD.")

# Check if all three categories have been chosen
if all(choice in Item_code for choice in [Choice1, Choice2, Choice3]):
    Total_price = price + 200  # Assuming a fixed additional cost of 200
    print("Total price for your computer is: ", Total_price)
else:
    print('Invalid input. Please choose one item from each category.')


TASK2:Ordering additional items.
Extend TASK 1 to:
allow a customer to choose whether to purchase any items from the other
categories – if so, which item(s)
update the price of the computer
store and output the additional items and the new price of the computer

CODE:
Item_code = ['A1', 'A2', 'B1', 'B2', 'B3', 'C1', 'C2', 'C3', 'D1', 'D2', 'E1', 'E2', 'E3', 'F1', 'F2', 'G1', 'G2']
Description = ['Compact', 'Tower', '8GB', '16GB', '32GB', '1 TB HDD', '2TB HDD', '4TB HDD', '240 GB SSD', '240 GB SSD',
               '1 TB HDD', '2TB HDD', '4TB HD', 'DVD/Blu-Ray Player', 'DVD/Blu-Ray Re-written', 'Standard Version',
               'Professional version']
Price = [75, 150, 79.99, 149.99, 299.99, 49.99, 89.99, 129.99, 59.99, 119.99, 49.99, 89.99, 129.99, 50, 100, 100, 175]

Choice1 = input("Please choose one case: ")
Choice2 = input("Please choose one RAM: ")
Choice3 = input("Please choose one HDD: ")

price = 0  # Initialize the price to 0

# Check choices and calculate the price
if Choice1 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice1)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for case.")

if Choice2 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice2)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for RAM.")

if Choice3 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice3)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for HDD.")

# Check if all three categories have been chosen
if all(choice in Item_code for choice in [Choice1, Choice2, Choice3]):
    Total_price = price + 200  # Assuming a fixed additional cost of 200
    print("Total price for your computer is: ", Total_price)
else:
    print('Invalid input. Please choose one item from each category.')

    
C = input("Would you like to choose any other item from additional items? ")
if(C=='Yes' or 'Y'):
  Choice4 = input("Please choose another item ")
  Choice5= input("Please enter any other item")
price2=0
# Check choices and calculate the price
if Choice4 in Item_code:
    price2 += Price[Item_code.index(Choice4)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for case.")

if Choice5 in Item_code:
    price2 += Price[Item_code.index(Choice5)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for case.")

# Check if all the categories have been chosen
if all(choice in Item_code for choice in [Choice4, Choice5]):
    Total_price = Total_price+price2 
    print("Total price for your computer is: ", Total_price)
else:
    print('Invalid input. Please choose one item from each category.')


TASK3: Offering discounts.
Extend TASK 2 to:
apply a 5% discount to the price of the computer if the customer has bought only
one additional item.
apply a 10% discount to the price of the computer if the customer has bought two
or more additional items.
output the amount of money saved and the new price of the computer after the
discount.

CODE:

Item_code = ['A1', 'A2', 'B1', 'B2', 'B3', 'C1', 'C2', 'C3', 'D1', 'D2', 'E1', 'E2', 'E3', 'F1', 'F2', 'G1', 'G2']
Description = ['Compact', 'Tower', '8GB', '16GB', '32GB', '1 TB HDD', '2TB HDD', '4TB HDD', '240 GB SSD', '240 GB SSD',
               '1 TB HDD', '2TB HDD', '4TB HD', 'DVD/Blu-Ray Player', 'DVD/Blu-Ray Re-written', 'Standard Version',
               'Professional version']
Price = [75, 150, 79.99, 149.99, 299.99, 49.99, 89.99, 129.99, 59.99, 119.99, 49.99, 89.99, 129.99, 50, 100, 100, 175]

Choice1 = input("Please choose one case: ")
Choice2 = input("Please choose one RAM: ")
Choice3 = input("Please choose one HDD: ")

price = 0  # Initialize the price to 0

# Check choices and calculate the price
if Choice1 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice1)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for case.")

if Choice2 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice2)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for RAM.")

if Choice3 in Item_code:
    price += Price[Item_code.index(Choice3)]
else:
    print("Invalid input for HDD.")

# Check if all three categories have been chosen
if all(choice in Item_code for choice in [Choice1, Choice2, Choice3]):
    Total_price = price + 200  # Assuming a fixed additional cost of 200
    print("Total price for your computer is: ", Total_price)

    # Additional items and discount logic
    Additional_item1 = input("Would you like to choose any other item from additional items? ")
    price2 = 0

    if Additional_item1.lower() == 'yes':
        Choice4 = input("Please choose another item ")
        if Choice4 in Item_code:
            price2 += Price[Item_code.index(Choice4)]

        Additional_item2 = input("Would you like to choose any other item from additional items? ")

        if Additional_item2.lower() == 'yes':
            Choice5 = input("Please choose another item ")
            if Choice5 in Item_code:
                price2 += Price[Item_code.index(Choice5)]

        # Calculate discount based on the number of additional items
        if Additional_item1.lower() == 'yes' and Additional_item2.lower() == 'yes':
            Total_price += price2
            Total = Total_price * 0.1
        elif Additional_item1.lower() == 'yes' or Additional_item2.lower() == 'yes':
            Total_price += price2
            Total = Total_price * 0.05
        else:
            Total = 0

        Grand_Total = Total_price - Total
        print("Grand Total with discount is", Grand_Total)

    elif Additional_item1.lower() == 'no':
        Total = Total_price * 0.05
        Grand_Total = Total_price - Total
        print("Grand Total with 5% discount is", Grand_Total)

    else:
        print("Invalid input for additional item.")
else:
    print('Invalid input. Please choose one item from each category.')

